bilingual.target: 他赢得了诺贝尔和平奖。

bilingual.source: The prize is for Jodie and me!
And maybe you will win a prize.
bilingual.target: 也许你会赢得一个奖品。
一等奖是“我的梦想假期”。

bilingual.source: And the winner always gets a very good prize.
bilingual.target: 而且获胜者总是能得到一个很好的奖品。

bilingual.source: She deserves this prize for all her hard work.
bilingual.target: 她应得这个奖，因为她的努力工作。

bilingual.source: The photo won the first prize in the competition.
bilingual.target: 这张照片在比赛中获得了一等奖。

bilingual.source: Li Bo won first prize in a Beijing opera competition.
bilingual.target: 李波在京剧比赛中获得了一等奖。

bilingual.source: Amy recently won a prize from the Help Save Our Planet Society.
bilingual.target: 艾米最近赢得了拯救地球协会的奖项。

bilingual.source: They were happy to know that they won the first prize last week.
bilingual.target: 他们很高兴知道他们上周赢得了一等奖。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, well, enjoy your prize.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，享用战利品。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, Daddy, I haven't won a prize yet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，爸爸，我一个奖都没拿到。

yingyinNormal.en: You're my prize pupils. Your prized what?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们是我最棒的学生，你最棒的什么？

yingyinNormal.en: That's a poor prize to take back to the Shire.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就带这么点纪念品回夏尔也未免太寒酸了。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies》

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, there's my prize. The royal blue tang fish. $500.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是我的珍宝，我的品蓝色拟刺尾鲷，花了五百块呢。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, Moon. What's the story? Is the prize really inside this thing? The prize? Oh, sure. Yes, it's all in there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是什么？这里面真的有奖金吗？奖金？当然啦。全在里面了。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, no. This is only the prize for the best tortoise. The prize for the best fish goes to Goldie the fish. Hooray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，不是，这奖励仅仅是送给最佳的乌龟的奖。最佳鱼类的获奖者是金金。太棒了！

yingyinNormal.en: I win the Nobel Prize for Physics. Not yet. Get to it!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我赢得诺贝尔物理学奖。还没到时候。那就赶紧啊！

yingyinNormal.en: The prize for the best gecko goes to the gecko. Hooray. The prize for the pet who looks most like a stick goes to Steven. Hooray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 获得最佳壁虎类奖励的是埃德蒙的庇护。太棒了！现在颁发的是最佳棍子模仿奖，我把它颁发给史蒂夫。太棒了！

yingyinNormal.en: I love the school sports day. Especially when I win a prize.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我很喜欢学校的运动会。特别是当我也得了奖的时候。

yingyinNormal.en: Look at Dr. Saul Perlmutter up there, clutching that Nobel Prize.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你看看索尔·珀尔马特，紧紧地抓着奖杯。

yingyinNormal.en: The prize for the best monkey... Doctor Hamster, he's not a real monkey. He's just pretend. The prize for the best pretend monkey goes to Monkey. Hooray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在我来颁发最佳猴子奖。仓鼠兽医，他不是一只真的猴子，他是一只假的猴子。那么最佳猴子伪装奖就是你了，佐伊的猴子。太好了!

yingyinNormal.en: You know any prize lawyers gonna take on two foster kids from the hood?
yingyinNormal.zh: 有几个大牌律师会正眼看待两个寄养儿童呢？

yingyinNormal.en: Really? Did you just have the Nobel Prize in waitressing stolen from you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 真的吗？你刚刚被人抢走了服务员的诺贝尔奖吗？

yingyinNormal.en: It's the first time the Carnegie Prize has been split. Hansen's all bent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这可是第一次，将卡内基奖学金平分。 汉森早已做好了决定。

yingyinNormal.en: I've brought my pet too, Tiddles the Tortoise. He likes climbing trees and... Who is the winner? Yes, who's won the prize? Now, the prize goes to Tiddles the Tortoise.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我把我的宠物带来了，它叫做乌龟小土豆。小土豆非常喜欢爬树，然后。。。谁赢了比赛？没错，谁赢得了奖励？嗯，获得奖励的人就是我的乌龟小土豆。

yingyinNormal.en: The universe has judged you. You asked it for a prize, and it told you no.
yingyinNormal.zh: 宇宙已对你作出了评判。你想得到奖赏，而它拒绝了你。

yingyinNormal.en: If he finds me before midnight when the masks come off, he can claim his prize.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果在半夜大家把面具摘下来之前他找到我了，他就能得到一点小奖励。

yingyinNormal.en: If true, that seems like an awfully large gamble given that the prize is Leonard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果这是真的，考虑到奖品只是莱纳德，你这个赌注貌似下得大了点。

yingyinNormal.en: I thought you were sweet on me. Okay, fine, let's say you never win a Nobel Prize.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不是爱我的吗？好吧,假设你这辈子没有赢得诺贝尔奖。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The Breakthrough <highlight>Prize</highlight> in Life Sciences, launched this year, takes an unrepresentative view of what the life sciences include.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今年推出的生命科学突破奖对生命科学的内容采取了一种不具代表性的观点。

examination_example.sentence: First, most researchers would accept such a <highlight>prize</highlight> if they were offered one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首先，如果能得到这样的奖励，大多数研究人员都会接受。

examination_example.sentence: As Nature has pointed out before, there are some legitimate concerns about how science <highlight>prizes</highlight> — both new and old — are distributed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 正如《自然》杂志以前已经指出的那样，对于科学奖项——新设的和原有的——如何分配，存在某些忧虑是合理的。

examination_example.sentence: Across generational lines, Americans continue to <highlight>prize</highlight> many of the same traditional milestones of a successful life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 跨越几代人的界限，美国人继续珍视许多成功人生的传统标志。

word_usage.usage: prize表示“奖；奖项；奖品”时，为可数名词。
prize作动词时，意思是“珍视；珍惜”，是及物动词，接名词或代词作宾语，可用于被动结构。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The problem with a company culture that <highlight>prizes</highlight> directness above all else is that it creates a toxic culture.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个重视直率高于一切的公司文化的问题在于，它创造了一种有害的文化。

examination_example.sentence: American designers <highlight>prized</highlight> resourcefulness and the freedom of women who wore the clothing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国设计师非常重视穿衣服的女性的智慧和自由。

examination_example.sentence: Panini's Ancient Rome and Modern Rome represent the sights most <highlight>prized</highlight>, including celebrated Greco-Roman statues and views of famous ruins, fountains, and churches.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 帕尼尼(Panini)的古罗马和现代罗马代表了最受瞩目的景点，包括著名的希腊罗马雕像，著名的遗址、喷泉和教堂等景色。

examination_example.sentence: Grand <highlight>Prizes</highlight>: Trip to Washington, D.C. for each of three winners, a parent and one other person of the winner's choice.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大奖：前往华盛顿特区为每三个获奖者，家长和另一个人的获胜者的选择。

examination_example.sentence: How many people can each grand <highlight>prize</highlight> winner take on the free trip?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每个大奖得主可以带多少人参加免费旅行？

examination_example.sentence: First <highlight>Prizes</highlight>: The book Sky Pioneer: A Photobiography of Amelia Earhart signed by author Corinne Szabo and pilot Linda Finch.

examination_example.sentence: I won the first <highlight>prize</highlight> in the swimming competition.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我在游泳比赛中获得一等奖。

examination_example.sentence: A year later, Hemingway won the Nobel <highlight>Prize</highlight> for Literature.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一年后，海明威获得了诺贝尔文学奖。

examination_example.sentence: "I will give a <highlight>prize</highlight> to the person who can solve my riddle, " the king said.
examination_example.sentence_trans: “我会给能解答我的谜语的人一份奖品，”国王说。
